I built a complete backend for my AI therapy chatbot using Node.js, MongoDB Atlas,
and the OpenAI API. When a user sends a message, my server saves it to the database, sends it to OpenAI for a response,
stores the AIâ€™s reply, and returns it to the client. I also separated the database logic into its own file (db.js)
and kept the API logic in server.js. With this setup, I now have a fully connected system where every user and AI message
is stored and can be retrieved at any time and it is open 24/7.